channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)

item.title: Tailoring Visual Object Representations to Human Requirements: A Case Study with a Recycling Robot
item.description: Robots are well-suited to alleviate the burden of repetitive and tedious manipulation tasks.

item.title: Dilation-Erosion for Single-Frame Supervised Temporal Action Localization
item.description: To balance the annotation labor and the granularity of supervision, single-frame annotation has been introduced in temporal action localization.

item.title: DA Wand: Distortion-Aware Selection using Neural Mesh Parameterization
item.description: We present a neural technique for learning to select a local sub-region around a point which can be used for mesh parameterization.

item.title: Diverse Demonstrations Improve In-context Compositional Generalization
item.description: In-context learning has shown great success in i. i. d semantic parsing splits, where the training and test sets are drawn from the same distribution.

item.title: Can recurrent neural networks learn process model structure?
item.description: In this work, we investigate the capabilities of such an LSTM to actually learn the underlying process model structure of an event log.

item.title: Category Theory for Quantum Natural Language Processing
item.description: The second chapter uses DisCopy to implement QNLP models as parameterised functors from grammar to quantum circuits.

item.title: What do Vision Transformers Learn? A Visual Exploration
item.description: In addition, we show that ViTs maintain spatial information in all layers except the final layer.

item.title: AdvMIL: Adversarial Multiple Instance Learning for the Survival Analysis on Whole-Slide Images
item.description: The survival analysis on histological whole-slide images (WSIs) is one of the most important means to estimate patient prognosis.

item.title: GPViT: A High Resolution Non-Hierarchical Vision Transformer with Group Propagation
item.description: In each GP Block, features are first grouped together by a fixed number of learnable group tokens; we then perform Group Propagation where global information is exchanged between the grouped features; finally, global information in the updated grouped features is returned back to the image features through a transformer decoder.

item.title: Unfolding Local Growth Rate Estimates for (Almost) Perfect Adversarial Detection
item.description: Convolutional neural networks (CNN) define the state-of-the-art solution on many perceptual tasks.

item.title: FastMIM: Expediting Masked Image Modeling Pre-training for Vision
item.description: This paper presents FastMIM, a simple and generic framework for expediting masked image modeling with the following two steps: (i) pre-training vision backbones with low-resolution input images; and (ii) reconstructing Histograms of Oriented Gradients (HOG) feature instead of original RGB values of the input images.

item.title: Regularized Optimal Transport Layers for Generalized Global Pooling Operations
item.description: Making the parameters of the ROT problem learnable, we develop a family of regularized optimal transport pooling (ROTP) layers.

item.title: Improving generalization in reinforcement learning through forked agents
item.description: An eco-system of agents each having their own policy with some, but limited, generalizability has proven to be a reliable approach to increase generalization across procedurally generated environments.

item.title: Structured Prompting: Scaling In-Context Learning to 1,000 Examples
item.description: Large language models have exhibited intriguing in-context learning capability, achieving promising zero- and few-shot performance without updating the parameters.

item.title: Learning 3D Representations from 2D Pre-trained Models via Image-to-Point Masked Autoencoders
item.description: Pre-training by numerous image data has become de-facto for robust 2D representations.

item.title: DifFace: Blind Face Restoration with Diffused Error Contraction
item.description: Moreover, the transition distribution can contract the error of the restoration backbone and thus makes our method more robust to unknown degradations.

item.title: A Statistical Model for Predicting Generalization in Few-Shot Classification
item.description: Such a set is hardly available in few-shot learning scenarios, a highly disregarded shortcoming in the field.

item.title: Predicting Knowledge Gain for MOOC Video Consumption
item.description: Informal learning on the Web using search engines as well as more structured learning on MOOC platforms have become very popular in recent years.

item.title: Score-based Generative Modeling Secretly Minimizes the Wasserstein Distance
item.description: Specifically, we prove that the Wasserstein distance is upper bounded by the square root of the objective function up to multiplicative constants and a fixed constant offset.

item.title: Distantly-Supervised Named Entity Recognition with Adaptive Teacher Learning and Fine-grained Student Ensemble
item.description: Distantly-Supervised Named Entity Recognition (DS-NER) effectively alleviates the data scarcity problem in NER by automatically generating training samples.

item.title: Prescriptive Process Monitoring in Intelligent Process Automation with Chatbot Orchestration
item.description: Using this dataset, we demonstrate crowd-wisdom and goal-driven approaches to prescriptive process monitoring.

item.title: Multi-objective Tree-structured Parzen Estimator Meets Meta-learning
item.description: Hyperparameter optimization (HPO) is essential for the better performance of deep learning, and practitioners often need to consider the trade-off between multiple metrics, such as error rate, latency, memory requirements, robustness, and algorithmic fairness.

item.title: Graph Convolutional Networks for Traffic Forecasting with Missing Values
item.description: To this end, we propose GCN-M, a Graph Convolutional Network model with the ability to handle the complex missing values in the Spatio-temporal context.

item.title: Multi-Dimensional Self Attention based Approach for Remaining Useful Life Estimation
item.description: We investigated the mainstream RUL prediction models and summarized the basic steps of RUL prediction modeling in this scenario.

item.title: Parameter-Efficient Finetuning of Transformers for Source Code
item.description: Pretrained Transformers achieve state-of-the-art performance in various code-processing tasks but may be too large to be deployed.

item.title: Reinforcement Learning and Tree Search Methods for the Unit Commitment Problem
item.description: When generator outages are considered, guided tree search saves over 2\% in operating costs as compared with methods using conventional $N-x$ reserve criteria.

item.title: Hardware-efficient learning of quantum many-body states
item.description: Efficient characterization of highly entangled multi-particle systems is an outstanding challenge in quantum science.

item.title: Zero-Shot Motor Health Monitoring by Blind Domain Transition
item.description: To address this need, in this pilot study, we propose a zero-shot bearing fault detection method that can detect any fault on a new (target) machine regardless of the working conditions, sensor parameters, or fault characteristics.

item.title: Collaborating Heterogeneous Natural Language Processing Tasks via Federated Learning
item.description: In this study, we further broaden the application scope of FL in NLP by proposing an Assign-Then-Contrast (denoted as ATC) framework, which enables clients with heterogeneous NLP tasks to construct an FL course and learn useful knowledge from each other.

item.title: Optimal Planning of Hybrid Energy Storage Systems using Curtailed Renewable Energy through Deep Reinforcement Learning
item.description: Energy management systems (EMS) are becoming increasingly important in order to utilize the continuously growing curtailed renewable energy.

item.title: Robust Recurrent Neural Network to Identify Ship Motion in Open Water with Performance Guarantees -- Technical Report
item.description: In this work, we represent a recurrent neural network as a linear time-invariant system with nonlinear disturbances.

item.title: Graph algorithms for predicting subcellular localization at the pathway level
item.description: Protein subcellular localization is an important factor in normal cellular processes and disease.

item.title: In Defense of Cross-Encoders for Zero-Shot Retrieval
item.description: We find that the number of parameters and early query-document interactions of cross-encoders play a significant role in the generalization ability of retrieval models.

item.title: RPN: A Word Vector Level Data Augmentation Algorithm in Deep Learning for Language Understanding
item.description: In subsequent experiments, we found that adding RPN to the training or fine-tuning model resulted in a stable boost on all 8 natural language processing tasks, including TweetEval, CoLA, and SST-2 datasets, and more significant improvements than other data augmentation algorithms. The RPN algorithm applies to all sentence-level tasks for language understanding and is used in any deep learning model with a word embedding layer.

item.title: The Stable Artist: Steering Semantics in Diffusion Latent Space
item.description: Large, text-conditioned generative diffusion models have recently gained a lot of attention for their impressive performance in generating high-fidelity images from text alone.

item.title: NMS Strikes Back
item.description: Our detector that trains Deformable-DETR with traditional IoU-based label assignment achieved 50. 2 COCO mAP within 12 epochs (1x schedule) with ResNet50 backbone, outperforming all existing traditional or transformer-based detectors in this setting.

item.title: Comparison Of Deep Object Detectors On A New Vulnerable Pedestrian Dataset
item.description: YOLOX consistently outperforms all other detectors on the mAP (0. 5:0. 95) per class metric, obtaining 0. 5644, 0. 5242, 0. 4781, and 0. 6796 for Children Without Disability, Elderly Without Disability, Non-vulnerable, and With Disability, respectively.

item.title: Automated ICD Coding using Extreme Multi-label Long Text Transformer-based Models
item.description: XR-Transformer, the new SOTA model in the general extreme multi-label text classification domain, and XR-LAT, a novel adaptation of the XR-Transformer model, were also trained on the MIMIC-III dataset.

item.title: Is ProtoPNet Really Explainable? Evaluating and Improving the Interpretability of Prototypes
item.description: ProtoPNet and its follow-up variants (ProtoPNets) have attracted broad research interest for their intrinsic interpretability from prototypes and comparable accuracy to non-interpretable counterparts.

item.title: SRoUDA: Meta Self-training for Robust Unsupervised Domain Adaptation
item.description: In this paper, we present a new meta self-training pipeline, named SRoUDA, for improving adversarial robustness of UDA models.

item.title: Resolving Semantic Confusions for Improved Zero-Shot Detection
item.description: Zero-shot detection (ZSD) is a challenging task where we aim to recognize and localize objects simultaneously, even when our model has not been trained with visual samples of a few target ("unseen") classes.

item.title: Video Prediction by Efficient Transformers
item.description: Video prediction is a challenging computer vision task that has a wide range of applications.

item.title: CLIP Itself is a Strong Fine-tuner: Achieving 85.7% and 88.0% Top-1 Accuracy with ViT-B and ViT-L on ImageNet
item.description: Recent studies have shown that CLIP has achieved remarkable success in performing zero-shot inference while its fine-tuning performance is not satisfactory.

item.title: ALSO: Automotive Lidar Self-supervision by Occupancy estimation
item.description: The core idea is to train the model on a pretext task which is the reconstruction of the surface on which the 3D points are sampled, and to use the underlying latent vectors as input to the perception head.

item.title: Deep learning-based Subtyping of Atypical and Normal Mitoses using a Hierarchical Anchor-Free Object Detector
item.description: In this work, we perform, for the first time, automatic subtyping of mitotic figures into normal and atypical categories according to characteristic morphological appearances of the different phases of mitosis.

item.title: HOTCOLD Block: Fooling Thermal Infrared Detectors with a Novel Wearable Design
item.description: Adversarial attacks on thermal infrared imaging expose the risk of related applications.

item.title: Masked autoencoders are effective solution to transformer data-hungry
item.description: This results in ViT not performing as well as CNNs on small datasets like medicine and science.

item.title: REAP: A Large-Scale Realistic Adversarial Patch Benchmark
item.description: In this work, we propose the REAP (REalistic Adversarial Patch) benchmark, a digital benchmark that allows the user to evaluate patch attacks on real images, and under real-world conditions.

item.title: MoDem: Accelerating Visual Model-Based Reinforcement Learning with Demonstrations
item.description: We identify key ingredients for leveraging demonstrations in model learning -- policy pretraining, targeted exploration, and oversampling of demonstration data -- which forms the three phases of our model-based RL framework.

item.title: Tensor-based Sequential Learning via Hankel Matrix Representation for Next Item Recommendations
item.description: Self-attentive transformer models have recently been shown to solve the next item recommendation task very efficiently.
